        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 5:10PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 510 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Abo, or 30 miles southwest of Estancia, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Abo.

This includes Highway 60 between Mile Markers 192 and 200.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rains from severe thunderstorms can produce sudden and
dangerous flows in arroyos, ditches and over low water crossings. Do
not attempt to drive through areas where water covers the roadway.</instruction>
